{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/77823", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/77823/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/77823/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/77823/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/77823", "id": 718877991, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU3MTg4Nzc5OTE=", "number": 77823, "title": "Python-like chained comparison operators", "user": {"login": "mayabyte", "id": 42569602, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQyNTY5NjAy", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42569602?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte", "html_url": "https://github.com/mayabyte", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mayabyte/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2020-10-11T16:51:51Z", "updated_at": "2020-10-11T17:09:08Z", "closed_at": "2020-10-11T16:57:54Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Python allows chaining comparison operators as a helpful shorthand:\r\n```python\r\nif a < b < c:  # equivalent to (a < b and b < c)\r\n    ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever Rust explicitly disallows this:\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    5 < 10 < 15\r\n}\r\n\r\n// error: comparison operators cannot be chained\r\n// --> chain.rs:2:5\r\n//  |\r\n// 2 |   5 < 10 < 15\r\n//  |     ^    ^\r\n//  |\r\n// help: split the comparison into two\r\n//  |\r\n// 2 |   5 < 10 && 10 < 15\r\n//  |          ^^^^^\r\n//\r\n// error: aborting due to previous error\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/558 seems to be the source of this explicit disallow, with the primary motivation being confusing behavior: `a < b < c` used to be interpreted as `(a < b) < c`, resulting in a type error. The RFC also claims this would allow implentation of Python-like chained comparison operators in the future. Is there any motivation not to add these Python-like chained comparison operators into Rust? Given that the syntax for it has been a compiler error since pre-1.0, it doesn't seem like it could be a breaking change. Thoughts?", "closed_by": {"login": "jonas-schievink", "id": 1786438, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODY0Mzg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1786438?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonas-schievink", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {